{
  "stem": "10588.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] is a dish of potatoes, and meat, and beans, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you take it Friday to bring it to the baker, because you don't cook on Shabbas.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And on Saturday, you go to the baker.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's [INAUDIBLE] you bring it after-- you-- the poorest families were rich on Shabbas.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because you would prepare, and you would save all things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You try to have traditional meals.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You go to shul.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You dress up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Shabbas was a day of rest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Usually when the-- when the-- my father, before he went to shul, first he went to shul.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We lit the candle for went to shul.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He-- he used to give everybody a hug and blessed us, and went to shul.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We came home.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had a beautiful Friday night traditional meal, you know, with gefilte fish, with chicken soup, and [INAUDIBLE], you know, and all the goodies.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we binged, and we used to sing songs and used to tell stories.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And whenever dad, my tatesh-- tatesh, we used to call them, mamesh and tatesh in yiddish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Would be always affectionate-- go to shul.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He would bring home an oyrekh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "An oyrekh is a guest.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A guest, why?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because there was some yeshivas.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was only synagogue with yeshivas.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So some boys would come to study.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would follow him home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, a lot of poor people stood at the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't have enough to eat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So always we would have a guest for Friday night, would bring home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, would be lots of story telling, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I just, I grew up with stories, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were singing, we were talking, reminiscing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to Hebrew school, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Beth Yakov ?].",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
